availableParameters.description: Detour to avoid traveling across walls, which may cause blobs on the surface.

availableParameters.name: curr_bed_type

availableParameters.description: Bed types supported by the printer.

availableParameters.name: other_layers_print_sequence_nums

availableParameters.name: before_layer_change_gcode

availableParameters.description: This G-code is inserted at every layer change before the Z lift.

availableParameters.name: enable_overhang_bridge_fan
availableParameters.title: Force cooling for overhangs and bridges

availableParameters.name: overhang_fan_speed
availableParameters.title: Overhangs and external bridges fan speed

availableParameters.name: set_other_flow_ratios
availableParameters.title: Set other flow ratios
availableParameters.description: Change flow ratios for other extrusion path types.

availableParameters.name: only_one_wall_top
availableParameters.title: Only one wall on top surfaces
availableParameters.description: Use only one wall on flat top surfaces, to give more space to the top infill pattern.

availableParameters.name: only_one_wall_first_layer
availableParameters.title: Only one wall on first layer
availableParameters.description: Use only one wall on first layer, to give more space to the bottom infill pattern.

availableParameters.name: extra_perimeters_on_overhangs
availableParameters.title: Extra perimeters on overhangs
availableParameters.description: Create additional perimeter paths over steep overhangs and areas where bridges cannot be anchored.

availableParameters.name: overhang_reverse
availableParameters.title: Reverse on even
availableParameters.description: Extrude perimeters that have a part over an overhang in the reverse direction on even layers. This alternating pattern can drastically improve steep overhangs.  This setting can also help reduce part warping due to the reduction of stresses in the part walls.

availableParameters.name: enable_overhang_speed
availableParameters.title: Slow down for overhang
availableParameters.description: Enable this option to slow printing down for different overhang degree.

availableParameters.name: internal_bridge_speed
availableParameters.title: Internal
availableParameters.description: Speed of internal bridges. If the value is expressed as a percentage, it will be calculated based on the bridge_speed. Default value is 150%.

availableParameters.name: brim_width
availableParameters.title: Brim width
availableParameters.description: Distance from model to the outermost brim line.

availableParameters.name: brim_object_gap
availableParameters.title: Brim-object gap
availableParameters.description: A gap between innermost brim line and object can make brim be removed more easily.

availableParameters.name: brim_ears
availableParameters.title: Brim ears
availableParameters.description: Only draw brim over the sharp edges of the model.

availableParameters.name: print_sequence
availableParameters.title: Print sequence
availableParameters.description: Print sequence, layer by layer or object by object.

availableParameters.name: print_order
availableParameters.title: Intra-layer order
availableParameters.description: Print order within a single layer.

availableParameters.name: slow_down_for_layer_cooling
availableParameters.title: Slow printing down for better layer cooling

availableParameters.name: default_acceleration
availableParameters.title: Normal printing
availableParameters.description: The default acceleration of both normal printing and travel except initial layer.

availableParameters.name: default_filament_profile
availableParameters.title: Default filament profile
availableParameters.description: Default filament profile when switching to this machine profile.

availableParameters.name: default_print_profile
availableParameters.title: Default process profile
availableParameters.description: Default process profile when switching to this machine profile.

availableParameters.name: activate_air_filtration
availableParameters.title: Activate air filtration
availableParameters.description: Activate for better air filtration. G-code command: M106 P3 S(0-255)

availableParameters.name: during_print_exhaust_fan_speed
availableParameters.title: Fan speed
availableParameters.description: Speed of exhaust fan during printing. This speed will override the speed in filament custom G-code.

availableParameters.name: complete_print_exhaust_fan_speed
availableParameters.title: Fan speed
availableParameters.description: Speed of exhaust fan after printing completes.

availableParameters.name: max_bridge_length
availableParameters.title: Max bridge length
availableParameters.description: Max length of bridges that don't need support. Set it to 0 if you want all bridges to be supported, and set it to a very large value if you don't want any bridges to be supported.

availableParameters.name: machine_end_gcode
availableParameters.title: End G-code
availableParameters.description: End G-code when finishing the entire print.

defaultValue.expression:
M104 S0 ; turn off temperature
G28 X0  ; home X axis
M84     ; disable motors

availableParameters.name: printing_by_object_gcode
availableParameters.title: Between Object G-code
availableParameters.description: Insert G-code between objects. This parameter will only come into effect when you print your models object by object.

availableParameters.name: filament_end_gcode
availableParameters.title: End G-code
availableParameters.description: End G-code when finishing the printing of this filament.

availableParameters.name: top_surface_pattern
availableParameters.title: Top surface pattern
availableParameters.description: Line pattern of top surface infill.

availableParameters.name: bottom_surface_pattern
availableParameters.title: Bottom surface pattern
availableParameters.description: Line pattern of bottom surface infill, not bridge infill.

availableParameters.name: internal_solid_infill_pattern
availableParameters.title: Internal solid infill pattern
availableParameters.description: Line pattern of internal solid infill. if the detect narrow internal solid infill be enabled, the concentric pattern will be used for the small area.

availableParameters.name: outer_wall_line_width
availableParameters.title: Outer wall
availableParameters.description: Line width of outer wall. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.

availableParameters.name: small_perimeter_threshold
availableParameters.title: Small perimeters threshold
availableParameters.description: This sets the threshold for small perimeter length. Default threshold is 0mm.

availableParameters.name: is_infill_first
availableParameters.title: Print infill first
availableParameters.description: Order of wall/infill. When the tickbox is unchecked the walls are printed first, which works best in most cases.  Printing infill first may help with extreme overhangs as the walls have the neighbouring infill to adhere to. However, the infill will slightly push out the printed walls where it is attached to them, resulting in a worse external surface finish. It can also cause the infill to shine through the external surfaces of the part.

availableParameters.name: wall_direction
availableParameters.title: Wall loop direction
availableParameters.description: The direction which the wall loops are extruded when looking down from the top.  By default all walls are extruded in counter-clockwise, unless Reverse on even is enabled. Set this to any option other than Auto will force the wall direction regardless of the Reverse on even.  This option will be disabled if spiral vase mode is enabled.

availableParameters.name: extruder_clearance_radius
availableParameters.title: Radius
availableParameters.description: Clearance radius around extruder. Used for collision avoidance in by-object printing.

availableParameters.name: nozzle_height
availableParameters.title: Nozzle height
availableParameters.description: The height of nozzle tip.

availableParameters.name: adaptive_bed_mesh_margin
availableParameters.title: Mesh margin
availableParameters.description: This option determines the additional distance by which the adaptive bed mesh area should be expanded in the XY directions.

availableParameters.name: extruder_colour
availableParameters.title: Extruder Color
availableParameters.description: Only used as a visual help on UI.

availableParameters.name: enable_pressure_advance
availableParameters.title: Enable pressure advance
availableParameters.description: Enable pressure advance, auto calibration result will be overwritten once enabled.

availableParameters.name: pressure_advance
availableParameters.title: Pressure advance
availableParameters.description: Pressure advance (Klipper) AKA Linear advance factor (Marlin).

availableParameters.name: adaptive_pressure_advance_overhangs
availableParameters.title: Enable adaptive pressure advance for overhangs (beta)

availableParameters.name: line_width
availableParameters.title: Default
availableParameters.description: Default line width if other line widths are set to 0. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.

availableParameters.name: filament_colour
availableParameters.title: Color
availableParameters.description: Only used as a visual help on UI.

availableParameters.name: filament_notes
availableParameters.title: Filament notes
availableParameters.description: You can put your notes regarding the filament here.

availableParameters.name: required_nozzle_HRC
availableParameters.title: Required nozzle HRC
availableParameters.description: Minimum HRC of nozzle required to print the filament. Zero means no checking of nozzle's HRC.

availableParameters.name: filament_map
availableParameters.title: Filament map to extruder
availableParameters.description: Filament map to extruder.

availableParameters.name: filament_flush_temp
availableParameters.title: Flush temperature
availableParameters.description: Temperature when flushing filament. 0 indicates the upper bound of the recommended nozzle temperature range.

availableParameters.name: filament_flush_volumetric_speed
availableParameters.title: Flush volumetric speed
availableParameters.description: Volumetric speed when flushing filament. 0 indicates the max volumetric speed.

availableParameters.name: bed_temperature_formula
availableParameters.title: Bed temperature type
availableParameters.description: This option determines how the bed temperature is set during slicing: based on the temperature of the first filament or the highest temperature of the printed filaments.

availableParameters.name: filament_diameter
availableParameters.title: Diameter
availableParameters.description: Filament diameter is used to calculate extrusion in G-code, so it is important and should be accurate.

availableParameters.name: pellet_flow_coefficient
availableParameters.title: Pellet flow coefficient
availableParameters.description: Pellet flow coefficient is empirically derived and allows for volume calculation for pellet printers.  Internally it is converted to filament_diameter. All other volume calculations remain the same.  filament_diameter = sqrt( (4 * pellet_flow_coefficient) / PI )

availableParameters.name: filament_adhesiveness_category
availableParameters.title: Adhesiveness Category
availableParameters.description: Filament category.

availableParameters.name: filament_loading_speed
availableParameters.title: Loading speed
availableParameters.description: Speed used for loading the filament on the wipe tower.

availableParameters.name: filament_loading_speed_start
availableParameters.title: Loading speed at the start
availableParameters.description: Speed used at the very beginning of loading phase.

availableParameters.name: filament_unloading_speed_start
availableParameters.title: Unloading speed at the start
availableParameters.description: Speed used for unloading the tip of the filament immediately after ramming.

availableParameters.name: filament_stamping_loading_speed
availableParameters.title: Stamping loading speed
availableParameters.description: Speed used for stamping.

availableParameters.name: filament_stamping_distance
availableParameters.title: Stamping distance measured from the center of the cooling tube

availableParameters.name: filament_cooling_initial_speed
availableParameters.title: Speed of the first cooling move
availableParameters.description: Cooling moves are gradually accelerating beginning at this speed.

availableParameters.name: filament_tower_interface_pre_extrusion_dist
availableParameters.title: Interface layer pre-extrusion distance
availableParameters.description: Pre-extrusion distance for prime tower interface layer (where different materials meet).

availableParameters.name: filament_tower_interface_pre_extrusion_length
availableParameters.title: Interface layer pre-extrusion length
availableParameters.description: Pre-extrusion length for prime tower interface layer (where different materials meet).

availableParameters.name: filament_tower_ironing_area

availableParameters.description: Ironing area for prime tower interface layer (where different materials meet).

availableParameters.name: filament_tower_interface_purge_volume
availableParameters.title: Interface layer purge length
availableParameters.description: Purge length for prime tower interface layer (where different materials meet).

availableParameters.title: Interface layer print temperature
availableParameters.description: Print temperature for prime tower interface layer (where different materials meet). If set to -1, use max recommended nozzle temperature.

availableParameters.name: filament_cooling_final_speed
availableParameters.title: Speed of the last cooling move
availableParameters.description: Cooling moves are gradually accelerating towards this speed.

availableParameters.name: filament_ramming_parameters
availableParameters.title: Ramming parameters
availableParameters.description: This string is edited by RammingDialog and contains ramming specific parameters.

availableParameters.title: Multi-tool ramming volume
availableParameters.description: The volume to be rammed before the tool change.

availableParameters.name: filament_multitool_ramming_flow
availableParameters.title: Multi-tool ramming flow
availableParameters.description: Flow used for ramming the filament before the tool change.

availableParameters.description: Filament density. For statistics only.

availableParameters.name: filament_type
availableParameters.title: Type
availableParameters.description: The material type of filament.

availableParameters.name: filament_soluble
availableParameters.title: Soluble material
availableParameters.description: Soluble material is commonly used to print supports and support interfaces.

availableParameters.name: filament_change_length
availableParameters.title: Filament ramming length
availableParameters.description: When changing the extruder, it is recommended to extrude a certain length of filament from the original extruder. This helps minimize nozzle oozing.

availableParameters.name: filament_is_support
availableParameters.title: Support material
availableParameters.description: Support material is commonly used to print supports and support interfaces.

availableParameters.name: filament_printable
availableParameters.title: Filament printable
availableParameters.description: The filament is printable in extruder.

availableParameters.name: filament_cost
availableParameters.title: Price
availableParameters.description: Filament price. For statistics only.

availableParameters.name: filament_vendor
availableParameters.title: Vendor
availableParameters.description: Vendor of filament. For show only.

availableParameters.name: infill_direction
availableParameters.title: Sparse infill direction
availableParameters.description: Angle for sparse infill pattern, which controls the start or main direction of line.

availableParameters.name: solid_infill_direction
availableParameters.title: Solid infill direction
availableParameters.description: Angle for solid infill pattern, which controls the start or main direction of line.

availableParameters.name: sparse_infill_density
availableParameters.title: Sparse infill density
availableParameters.description: Density of internal sparse infill, 100% turns all sparse infill into solid infill and internal solid infill pattern will be used.

availableParameters.name: align_infill_direction_to_model
availableParameters.title: Align infill direction to model
availableParameters.description: Aligns infill and surface fill directions to follow the model's orientation on the build plate. When enabled, fill directions rotate with the model to maintain optimal strength characteristics.

availableParameters.title: Insert solid layers
availableParameters.description: Insert solid infill at specific layers. Use N to insert every Nth layer, N#K to insert K consecutive solid layers every N layers (K is optional, e.g. '5#' equals '5#1'), or a comma-separated list (e.g. 1,7,9) to insert at explicit layers. Layers are 1-based.

availableParameters.name: fill_multiline
availableParameters.title: Fill Multiline
availableParameters.description: Using multiple lines for the infill pattern, if supported by infill pattern.

availableParameters.name: sparse_infill_pattern
availableParameters.title: Sparse infill pattern
availableParameters.description: Line pattern for internal sparse infill.

availableParameters.name: lateral_lattice_angle_1
availableParameters.title: Lateral lattice angle 1
availableParameters.description: The angle of the first set of Lateral lattice elements in the Z direction. Zero is vertical.

availableParameters.name: lateral_lattice_angle_2
availableParameters.title: Lateral lattice angle 2
availableParameters.description: The angle of the second set of Lateral lattice elements in the Z direction. Zero is vertical.

availableParameters.name: infill_overhang_angle
availableParameters.title: Infill overhang angle
availableParameters.description: The angle of the infill angled lines. 60° will result in a pure honeycomb.

availableParameters.name: infill_anchor_max

availableParameters.name: outer_wall_acceleration

availableParameters.name: bridge_acceleration
availableParameters.title: Bridge
availableParameters.description: Acceleration of bridges. If the value is expressed as a percentage (e.g. 50%), it will be calculated based on the outer wall acceleration.

availableParameters.name: sparse_infill_acceleration
availableParameters.title: Sparse infill
availableParameters.description: Acceleration of sparse infill. If the value is expressed as a percentage (e.g. 100%), it will be calculated based on the default acceleration.

availableParameters.name: internal_solid_infill_acceleration
availableParameters.title: Internal solid infill
availableParameters.description: Acceleration of internal solid infill. If the value is expressed as a percentage (e.g. 100%), it will be calculated based on the default acceleration.

availableParameters.name: initial_layer_acceleration
availableParameters.title: Initial layer
availableParameters.description: Acceleration of initial layer. Using a lower value can improve build plate adhesion.

availableParameters.name: accel_to_decel_enable
availableParameters.title: Enable accel_to_decel
availableParameters.description: Klipper's max_accel_to_decel will be adjusted automatically.

availableParameters.name: accel_to_decel_factor
availableParameters.title: accel_to_decel
availableParameters.description: Klipper's max_accel_to_decel will be adjusted to this %% of acceleration.

availableParameters.name: default_junction_deviation

availableParameters.description: Marlin Firmware Junction Deviation (replaces the traditional XY Jerk setting).

availableParameters.name: outer_wall_jerk
availableParameters.title: Outer wall

availableParameters.name: initial_layer_line_width
availableParameters.title: Initial layer
availableParameters.description: Line width of initial layer. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.

availableParameters.name: initial_layer_print_height
availableParameters.title: Initial layer height
availableParameters.description: Height of initial layer. Making initial layer height to be thick slightly can improve build plate adhesion.

availableParameters.name: initial_layer_speed
availableParameters.title: Initial layer
availableParameters.description: Speed of initial layer except the solid infill part.

availableParameters.name: initial_layer_infill_speed
availableParameters.title: Initial layer infill
availableParameters.description: Speed of solid infill part of initial layer.

availableParameters.name: initial_layer_travel_speed
availableParameters.title: Initial layer travel speed
availableParameters.description: Travel speed of initial layer.

availableParameters.name: nozzle_temperature_initial_layer
availableParameters.title: Initial layer
availableParameters.description: Nozzle temperature for printing initial layer when using this filament.

availableParameters.name: fuzzy_skin_thickness
availableParameters.title: Fuzzy skin thickness
availableParameters.description: The width within which to jitter. It's advised to be below outer wall line width.

availableParameters.name: fuzzy_skin_point_distance
availableParameters.title: Fuzzy skin point distance
availableParameters.description: The average distance between the random points introduced on each line segment.

availableParameters.name: fuzzy_skin_first_layer
availableParameters.title: Apply fuzzy skin to first layer
availableParameters.description: Whether to apply fuzzy skin on the first layer.

availableParameters.name: fuzzy_skin_scale
availableParameters.title: Fuzzy skin feature size
availableParameters.description: The base size of the coherent noise features, in mm. Higher values will result in larger features.

availableParameters.name: fuzzy_skin_octaves
availableParameters.title: Fuzzy Skin Noise Octaves
availableParameters.description: The number of octaves of coherent noise to use. Higher values increase the detail of the noise, but also increase computation time.

availableParameters.name: fuzzy_skin_persistence
availableParameters.title: Fuzzy skin noise persistence
availableParameters.description: The decay rate for higher octaves of the coherent noise. Lower values will result in smoother noise.

availableParameters.name: gap_infill_speed
availableParameters.title: Gap infill
availableParameters.description: Speed of gap infill. Gap usually has irregular line width and should be printed more slowly.

availableParameters.name: gcode_add_line_number
availableParameters.title: Add line number
availableParameters.description: Enable this to add line number(Nx) at the beginning of each G-code line.

availableParameters.name: scan_first_layer
availableParameters.title: Scan first layer
availableParameters.description: Enable this to enable the camera on printer to check the quality of first layer.

availableParameters.name: enable_power_loss_recovery
availableParameters.title: Power Loss Recovery
availableParameters.description: Choose how to control power loss recovery. When set to Printer configuration, the slicer will not emit power loss recovery G-code and will leave the printer's configuration unchanged. Applicable to Bambu Lab or Marlin 2 firmware based printers.

availableParameters.name: spaghetti_detector
availableParameters.title: Enable spaghetti detector
availableParameters.description: Enable the camera on printer to check spaghetti.

availableParameters.name: nozzle_hrc
availableParameters.title: Nozzle HRC
availableParameters.description: The nozzle's hardness. Zero means no checking for nozzle's hardness during slicing.

availableParameters.name: printer_structure
availableParameters.title: Printer structure
availableParameters.description: The physical arrangement and components of a printing device.

availableParameters.name: best_object_pos
availableParameters.title: Best object position
availableParameters.description: Best auto arranging position in range [0,1] w.r.t. bed shape.

availableParameters.name: auxiliary_fan
availableParameters.title: Auxiliary part cooling fan
availableParameters.description: Enable this option if machine has auxiliary part cooling fan. G-code command: M106 P2 S(0-255).

availableParameters.name: fan_speedup_overhangs
availableParameters.title: Only overhangs
availableParameters.description: Will only take into account the delay for the cooling of overhangs.

availableParameters.name: time_cost
availableParameters.title: Time cost
availableParameters.description: The printer cost per hour.

availableParameters.name: support_chamber_temp_control
availableParameters.title: Support control chamber temperature
availableParameters.description: This option is enabled if machine support controlling chamber temperature G-code command: M141 S(0-255)

availableParameters.name: support_air_filtration
availableParameters.title: Support air filtration
availableParameters.description: Enable this if printer support air filtration G-code command: M106 P3 S(0-255)

availableParameters.name: gcode_flavor

availableParameters.description: What kind of G-code the printer is compatible with.

availableParameters.name: pellet_modded_printer
availableParameters.title: Pellet Modded Printer
availableParameters.description: Enable this option if your printer uses pellets instead of filaments.

availableParameters.name: support_multi_bed_types
availableParameters.title: Support multi bed types
availableParameters.description: Enable this option if you want to use multiple bed types.

availableParameters.name: exclude_object

availableParameters.description: Enable this option to add EXCLUDE OBJECT command in G-code.

availableParameters.name: skin_infill_depth
availableParameters.title: Skin infill depth
availableParameters.description: The parameter sets the depth of skin.

availableParameters.name: infill_lock_depth
availableParameters.title: Infill lock depth
availableParameters.description: The parameter sets the overlapping depth between the interior and skin.

availableParameters.name: skin_infill_line_width
availableParameters.title: Skin line width
availableParameters.description: Adjust the line width of the selected skin paths.

availableParameters.name: skeleton_infill_line_width
availableParameters.title: Skeleton line width
availableParameters.description: Adjust the line width of the selected skeleton paths.

availableParameters.name: enable_wrapping_detection

availableParameters.description: Enable clumping detection

availableParameters.name: wrapping_detection_layers
availableParameters.title: Clumping detection layers
availableParameters.description: Clumping detection layers.

availableParameters.name: wrapping_exclude_area
availableParameters.title: Probing exclude area of clumping
availableParameters.description: Probing exclude area of clumping.

availableParameters.name: sparse_infill_filament
availableParameters.title: Infill
availableParameters.description: Filament to print internal sparse infill.

availableParameters.name: sparse_infill_line_width
availableParameters.title: Sparse infill
availableParameters.description: Line width of internal sparse infill. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.

availableParameters.name: sparse_infill_speed
availableParameters.title: Sparse infill
availableParameters.description: Speed of internal sparse infill.

availableParameters.name: inherits

availableParameters.description: Name of parent profile.

availableParameters.name: mmu_segmented_region_max_width

availableParameters.name: mmu_segmented_region_interlocking_depth
availableParameters.title: Interlocking depth of a segmented region

availableParameters.name: interlocking_beam
availableParameters.title: Use beam interlocking
availableParameters.description: Generate interlocking beam structure at the locations where different filaments touch. This improves the adhesion between filaments, especially models printed in different materials.

availableParameters.name: interlocking_beam_width
availableParameters.title: Interlocking beam width
availableParameters.description: The width of the interlocking structure beams.

availableParameters.name: interlocking_orientation
availableParameters.title: Interlocking direction
availableParameters.description: Orientation of interlock beams.

availableParameters.name: interlocking_beam_layer_count
availableParameters.title: Interlocking beam layers
availableParameters.description: The height of the beams of the interlocking structure, measured in number of layers. Less layers is stronger, but more prone to defects.

availableParameters.name: interlocking_depth
availableParameters.title: Interlocking depth
availableParameters.description: The distance from the boundary between filaments to generate interlocking structure, measured in cells. Too few cells will result in poor adhesion.

availableParameters.name: interlocking_boundary_avoidance

availableParameters.name: ironing_spacing

availableParameters.description: The distance between the lines of ironing.

availableParameters.description: The distance to keep from the edges. A value of 0 sets this to half of the nozzle diameter.

availableParameters.name: ironing_speed
availableParameters.title: Ironing speed
availableParameters.description: Print speed of ironing lines.

availableParameters.name: ironing_angle
availableParameters.title: Ironing angle offset
availableParameters.description: The angle of ironing lines offset from the top surface.

availableParameters.name: ironing_angle_fixed
availableParameters.title: Fixed ironing angle

availableParameters.name: autosave
availableParameters.title: Autosave
availableParameters.description: Automatically export current configuration to the specified file.

availableParameters.name: datadir
availableParameters.title: Data directory
availableParameters.description: Load and store settings at the given directory. This is useful for maintaining different profiles or including configurations from a network storage.

availableParameters.name: outputdir
availableParameters.title: Output directory
availableParameters.description: Output directory for the exported files.

availableParameters.name: debug
availableParameters.title: Debug level
availableParameters.description: Sets debug logging level. 0:fatal, 1:error, 2:warning, 3:info, 4:debug, 5:trace

availableParameters.name: enable_timelapse
availableParameters.title: Enable timelapse for print
availableParameters.description: If enabled, this slicing will be considered using timelapse.

availableParameters.name: sw_renderer
availableParameters.title: Render with a software renderer
availableParameters.description: Render with a software renderer. The bundled MESA software renderer is loaded instead of the default OpenGL driver.

availableParameters.name: load_custom_gcodes
availableParameters.title: Load custom G-code
availableParameters.description: Load custom G-code from json.

availableParameters.name: load_filament_ids
availableParameters.title: Load filament IDs
availableParameters.description: Load filament IDs for each object.

availableParameters.name: allow_multicolor_oneplate
availableParameters.title: Allow multiple colors on one plate
availableParameters.description: If enabled, Arrange will allow multiple colors on one plate.

availableParameters.name: allow_rotations
availableParameters.title: Allow rotation when arranging
availableParameters.description: If enabled, Arrange will allow rotation when placing objects.

availableParameters.name: avoid_extrusion_cali_region
availableParameters.title: Avoid extrusion calibrate region when arranging
availableParameters.description: If enabled, Arrange will avoid extrusion calibrate region when placing objects.

availableParameters.name: skip_modified_gcodes
availableParameters.title: Skip modified G-code in 3MF
availableParameters.description: Skip the modified G-code in 3MF from printer or filament presets.

availableParameters.name: makerlab_name
availableParameters.title: MakerLab name
availableParameters.description: MakerLab name to generate this 3MF.

availableParameters.name: makerlab_version
availableParameters.title: MakerLab version
availableParameters.description: MakerLab version to generate this 3MF.

availableParameters.name: metadata_name
availableParameters.title: Metadata name list
availableParameters.description: Metadata name list added into 3MF.

availableParameters.name: metadata_value
availableParameters.title: Metadata value list
availableParameters.description: Metadata value list added into 3MF.

availableParameters.name: allow_newer_file
availableParameters.title: Allow 3MF with newer version to be sliced
availableParameters.description: Allow 3MF with newer version to be sliced.

availableParameters.name: zhop
availableParameters.title: Current Z-hop
availableParameters.description: Contains Z-hop present at the beginning of the custom G-code block.

availableParameters.name: e_restart_extra
availableParameters.title: Extra de-retraction
availableParameters.description: Currently planned extra extruder priming after de-retraction.

availableParameters.name: e_position
availableParameters.title: Absolute E position
availableParameters.description: Current position of the extruder axis. Only used with absolute extruder addressing.

availableParameters.name: current_extruder
availableParameters.title: Current extruder
availableParameters.description: Zero-based index of currently used extruder.

availableParameters.name: current_object_idx
availableParameters.title: Current object index
availableParameters.description: Specific for sequential printing. Zero-based index of currently printed object.

availableParameters.name: has_wipe_tower
availableParameters.title: Has wipe tower
availableParameters.description: Whether or not wipe tower is being generated in the print.

availableParameters.name: initial_extruder
availableParameters.title: Initial extruder
availableParameters.description: Zero-based index of the first extruder used in the print. Same as initial_tool.

availableParameters.name: initial_tool
availableParameters.title: Initial tool
availableParameters.description: Zero-based index of the first extruder used in the print. Same as initial_extruder.

availableParameters.name: is_extruder_used
availableParameters.title: Is extruder used?
availableParameters.description: Vector of booleans stating whether a given extruder is used in the print.

availableParameters.name: num_extruders
availableParameters.title: Number of extruders
availableParameters.description: Total number of extruders, regardless of whether they are used in the current print.

availableParameters.name: initial_filament_type
availableParameters.title: Initial filament type
availableParameters.description: String containing filament type of the first used extruder.

availableParameters.name: has_single_extruder_multi_material_priming
availableParameters.title: Has single extruder MM priming
availableParameters.description: Are the extra multi-material priming regions used in this print?

availableParameters.name: extruded_volume
availableParameters.title: Volume per extruder
availableParameters.description: Total filament volume extruded per extruder during the entire print.

availableParameters.name: total_toolchanges
availableParameters.title: Total tool changes
availableParameters.description: Number of tool changes during the print.

availableParameters.name: extruded_volume_total
availableParameters.title: Total volume
availableParameters.description: Total volume of filament used during the entire print.

availableParameters.name: extruded_weight
availableParameters.title: Weight per extruder
availableParameters.description: Weight per extruder extruded during the entire print. Calculated from filament_density value in Filament Settings.

availableParameters.name: extruded_weight_total
availableParameters.title: Total weight
availableParameters.description: Total weight of the print. Calculated from filament_density value in Filament Settings.

availableParameters.name: total_layer_count
availableParameters.title: Total layer count
availableParameters.description: Number of layers in the entire print.

availableParameters.name: normal_print_time
availableParameters.title: Print time (normal mode)
availableParameters.description: Estimated print time when printed in normal mode (i.e. not in silent mode). Same as print_time.

availableParameters.name: num_printing_extruders
availableParameters.title: Number of printing extruders
availableParameters.description: Number of extruders used during the print.

availableParameters.name: print_time
availableParameters.title: Print time (normal mode)
availableParameters.description: Estimated print time when printed in normal mode (i.e. not in silent mode). Same as normal_print_time.

availableParameters.name: printing_filament_types
availableParameters.title: Used filament types
availableParameters.description: Comma-separated list of all filament types used during the print.

availableParameters.name: silent_print_time
availableParameters.title: Print time (silent mode)
availableParameters.description: Estimated print time when printed in silent mode.

availableParameters.name: total_cost
availableParameters.title: Total cost
availableParameters.description: Total cost of all material used in the print. Calculated from filament_cost value in Filament Settings.

availableParameters.name: total_weight
availableParameters.title: Total weight
availableParameters.description: Total weight of the print. Calculated from filament_density value in Filament Settings.

availableParameters.name: total_wipe_tower_cost
availableParameters.title: Total wipe tower cost
availableParameters.description: Total cost of the material wasted on the wipe tower. Calculated from filament_cost value in Filament Settings.

availableParameters.name: total_wipe_tower_filament
availableParameters.title: Wipe tower volume
availableParameters.description: Total filament volume extruded on the wipe tower.

availableParameters.name: used_filament
availableParameters.title: Used filament
availableParameters.description: Total length of filament used in the print.

availableParameters.name: print_time_sec
availableParameters.title: Print time (seconds)
availableParameters.description: Total estimated print time in seconds. Replaced with actual value during post-processing.

availableParameters.name: used_filament_length
availableParameters.title: Filament length (meters)
availableParameters.description: Total filament length used in meters. Replaced with actual value during post-processing.

availableParameters.name: num_objects
availableParameters.title: Number of objects
availableParameters.description: Total number of objects in the print.

availableParameters.name: num_instances
availableParameters.title: Number of instances
availableParameters.description: Total number of object instances in the print, summed over all objects.

availableParameters.name: input_filename_base
availableParameters.title: Input filename without extension
availableParameters.description: Source filename of the first object, without extension.

availableParameters.name: first_layer_print_min
availableParameters.title: Bottom-left corner of first layer bounding box

availableParameters.name: first_layer_print_max
availableParameters.title: Top-right corner of first layer bounding box

availableParameters.name: first_layer_print_size
availableParameters.title: Size of the first layer bounding box

availableParameters.name: print_bed_min
availableParameters.title: Bottom-left corner of print bed bounding box

availableParameters.name: print_bed_max
availableParameters.title: Top-right corner of print bed bounding box

availableParameters.name: print_bed_size
availableParameters.title: Size of the print bed bounding box

availableParameters.name: timestamp
availableParameters.title: Timestamp
availableParameters.description: String containing current time in yyyyMMdd-hhmmss format.

availableParameters.name: print_preset
availableParameters.title: Print preset name
availableParameters.description: Name of the print preset used for slicing.

availableParameters.name: printer_preset
availableParameters.title: Printer preset name
availableParameters.description: Name of the printer preset used for slicing.

availableParameters.name: physical_printer_preset
availableParameters.title: Physical printer name
availableParameters.description: Name of the physical printer used for slicing.

availableParameters.name: layer_num
availableParameters.title: Layer number
availableParameters.description: Index of the current layer. One-based (i.e. first layer is number 1).

availableParameters.name: layer_z
availableParameters.title: Layer Z
availableParameters.description: Height of the current layer above the print bed, measured to the top of the layer.

availableParameters.name: max_layer_z
availableParameters.title: Maximal layer Z
availableParameters.description: Height of the last layer above the print bed.

availableParameters.name: filament_extruder_id
availableParameters.title: Filament extruder ID
availableParameters.description: The current extruder ID. The same as current_extruder.
